README

By: Ari Brown

This is a basic game written in C++ using the SDL framework. Example of loading textures and
event-driven C++ programming.

Also an attempt at implementing some physics projectile equations into a game
(walk to the left at game startup to kick a soccer ball)

Basic features:

Startup scene: tree, bench, and birds
Right screen 1: house outdoors
Right screen 2: house indoors
Left screen 1: soccer ball and open field

Use arrow keys to move

-----------------------------------
Compile:
        clang++ -Wall -Wextra game.cpp -o game -F /Library/Frameworks -framework SDL2_image -framework SDL2

Run:
        ./game

Requirements:

SDL2 framework
SDL2_image framework
